extraInfo.description: Will Donald Trump win the 2020 U.S. Presidential election?
extraInfo.longDescription:
A candidate that receives at least 270 votes in the Electoral College shall be considered the winner. In the event that no candidate receives 270 votes, the House of Representatives will decide the winner. In the event of further indecision or tie, it will be the candidate determined to be the winner under the US Constitution.
This market is intended to be about a Single Candidate, if this is not the case, this market should settle as 'Invalid'.

extraInfo.description: Will the Democratic Party Control the Presidency, the Senate, and the House of Representatives on February 1st, 2021?
extraInfo.longDescription:
This market shall resolve as YES if and only if all three of the following conditions are true at 00:00 UTC on February 1st, 2021:

1. The last inaugurated president of the U.S. is affiliated with the U.S. Democratic Party.
2. The Senate Majority Leader is affiliated with the U.S. Democratic Party. 
3. The majority of voting members of the House of Representatives are affiliated with the U.S. Democratic Party
